Popular comedian, Francis Agoda aka I Go Dye has unveiled the artistes performing at his April 18th show holding in Benin City tagged “I Go Dye Standing: More than a Legend. In a statement in Benin City, the Edo State capital, the comedian who is also a global diplomat for advocate of peace, said that legendary musician 2Baba will be the opening act, I Go Save as host while Tiwa Savage will be on hand to also thrill the audience. The comedy impresario mentioned that other stars like Okey Bakassi will be among some of the A-list performers that will grace the stage of the highly publicised event.   Mr Eazi receives £1,000 as engagement gift     Osinachi’s death: Marriage good but not by force…     2022 slangs rocking Nigeria’s streets, social media   According to the multiple award-winning and widely travelled comedian, “I Go Dye Standing: More than a legend” will also give opportunities to budding talented acts to promote their crafts on stage. He said he chose to hold the show on Easter Sunday to buttress the fact that everyone can be given a second chance. I Go Dye further urged Christians and Nigerians at large to always imbibe the teachings of Jesus Christ which are embedded in love for all irrespective of religion, ethnicity or tribe.